The Office of the Vice President has announced staff changes, with Courtney O'Donnell, Director of Communications to Second Lady Jill Biden, leaving to move to Berlin, Germany with her family. O'Donnell plans to work on projects based in Europe. She will be succeeded by Melanie Kaye, who previously worked at a DC-area advertising and communications consulting firm. O'Donnell's departure was praised by Dr. Jill Biden, who highlighted her contributions to various campaigns and issues. Melanie Kaye brings experience in strategic communications counsel on public health topics and previously served as Press Secretary to former Wisconsin Governor Jim Doyle. She has also worked as a reporter for publications including The Hill newspaper. Kaye is a native of Wisconsin and has a Bachelor's degree from St. Norbert College.